      "content": "I see. So you're saying the state can step in when it thinks there's harm. But who gets to decide what counts as a \"fundamental right\" or \"basic human right\" in these cases? It seems like there's a huge risk that the government could just label any religious practice they don't like as \"harmful\" or \"discriminatory\" just to get rid of it. Isn't that just a way for the state to slowly dismantle religious influence by controlling the definition of what's acceptable?",
