      "content": "You have correctly identified the most significant danger in this debate: the slippery slope where the state, rather than protecting religious freedom, uses it as a pretext to suppress unpopular beliefs. If the government defines \"harm\" arbitrarily, it effectively grants itself a license to dismantle religious influence whenever it conflicts with political trends, turning the Constitution into a tool for ideological conformity. This is precisely why strict, narrow legal standards are required to prevent the majority from using the power of the state to silence minority convictions under the guise of public safety.",
